{
  "stem": "5388.2",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They had a ghetto within a ghetto.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So they had a workers quarter where they gave people what they called a schein, which is like a certificate or something, a little card saying, let's say-- my father didn't have it, but let's assume that if you would have had it, it would have been written Hirsch Nussbaum and four people.",
      "word_count": 53
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So what happened was many people who worked-- so a brother, suddenly his sister was his wife.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Or if he was a little bit older, his mother was his wife, and that was his daughter.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I mean, people were trying to be on the list.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I was, at that time-- our friend from Raczki-- Ratzki is the Yiddish version of it-- was in one of those quarters.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I went over there to stay with them already, because it sounded like that that is a safer place, that they might not touch on because these are people working for the Germans.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They have certificates.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And it's separated already from the other ghettos.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My father was in hiding outside of the ghetto at some people that he knew on the-- on one side of the street was the Jewish ghetto, and the other side was not, was outside the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In Slonim, Pushkinskaya, Pushkin at the time.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And my sisters, too, were from some friends that we knew through then our landlord.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Our landlord was not a Jew.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He was white Russian.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Through his family.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So they went there, and I went to the Marianski's.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And you know, it was a safe place at that particular day.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And somehow or other, I figured, oh, I have to go and tell it to my father.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "He shouldn't come back to the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
